Frisco.Independence High School (Frisco, Texas): Independence High School is a public high school located in the city of Frisco, Texas (USA) and classified as a 5A school by UIL. It is a part of the Frisco Independent School District located in western Collin County. It opened in the fall of 2014 to freshmen, sophomore and junior students. The first class to graduate was the class of 2016. In 2015, the school was rated "Met Standard" by the Texas Education Agency.
